[2] Malaysia (national)
Date: Wed 26 Mar 2008
Source: NST Online [edited]
<http://www.nst.com.my/Current_News/NST/Wednesday/NewsBreak/20080326173057/Article/index_html>


Three more people lost their lives to dengue between 16 - 22 Mar
[2008], bringing the number of fatalities due to the disease to 8 so
far this year [2008]. The 1st fatality happened in the 3rd week of
January, another 2 in week 2 of February and 2 more in the 1st week of March.

Disease Conrtol Division director Datuk Dr Hasan Abdul Rahman,
however, said despite the fatalites recorded in the 3rd week of
March, the number of cases reported that week showed a drop, from 643
cases in week 2 to 573 cases, which translated into a 10.6 percent decrease.

Of the figure for week 3318 cases or 55.3 percent of the total were
reported in the states of Selangor, Kelantan, Malacca, Negri
Sembilan, Terengganu and the federal territory of Labuan, he said in
a statement here today [26 Mar 2008].

He added that monitoring by district health offices found houses and
shoplots to be the main culprits where breeding of the _Aedes_
mosquito (the [dengue virus] vector) was concerned.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

