[3] Philippines (Ilocos)
Date: Wed 26 Mar 2008
Source: ABS CBN [edited]
<http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/storypage.aspx?StoryId=113200>


The number of persons recorded this year [2008] to have been affected
by dengue fever in Ilocos Norte has already reached 90 with 2
confirmed to have died from the deadly disease.

The present figure was triple the number recorded in the 1st quarter
of 2007. Batac City was reported to have had the highest number of
cases with 27. Laoag City was 2nd with 12 cases.

Due to this alarming figures, the Region 1 office of the Department
of Health and Ilocos Norte Provincial Health Office are making the
rounds to provide residents of the province with tips to prevent the
spread of the disease.

[Byline: Randy Menor]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur Brent Barrett

[A map of Philippine provinces, showing Ilocos Norte, in far NW
Philippines, can be accessed at
<http://www.reliefweb.int/mapc/asi_se/cnt/phil/phl_ad.html>. - Mod.TY]

