[10] Brazil (national)
Date: Wed 26 Mar 2008
Source: EER Noticias [in Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.TY]
<http://www.paho.org:80/spanish/ad/dpc/cd/eid-eer-2008-03-26.htm>


Since 01 Jan 2008 the Brazilian health authorities have reported 406
DHF cases, with 34 deaths nationally. There is a noteworthy increase
in [dengue] cases in various states in the country compared to the
same period in 2007; Amazonas (an increase of 9.8 times), Rondonia
(5.3 times), Sergipe (4.7 times), Bahia (3.4 times), Rio Grande do
Norte (2.8 times), Para (2.5 times) y Rio de Janeiro (2.2 times).

The state of Rio de Janeiro has reported 32 615 cases of dengue fever
corresponding to 38 percent of the total cases reported in the
country), and 245 cases of DHF. Of those affected, a change in
serious cases has been observed. Of the 2116 hospitalized cases, 53
were children under 14 years [of age]. Of the total registered
deaths, 20 were due to DHF, 8 to dengue shock syndrome, and 19 from
complications of dengue [virus] infection. More than 50 percent of
the deaths occurred in children 2-13 years old. The increase in the
number of registered deaths suggests that there has been a greater
evolution in severity of clinical manifestations than was expected.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur Marianne Hopp
<promed@promedmail.org>
